# This project's own flake.nix defines the browser; direnv just loads it.
# You never reference the multi-profile engine here — flake.nix does that.
#
# A bare `use flake` loads the default devShell. Since this project defines a
# single profile, that shell carries the short `web` command.

use flake

# Then run `web` in this directory. The runtime profile (cookies, sessions,
# logins) lives in ./.direnv/browser-profiles/<name>/ — local to this direnv.
